definition.value: A UDP-amino sugar having 2,4-diacetamido-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose as the amino sugar component.

A member of the class of cortistatins that is substituted by a dimethylamino group at the 3alpha position and a (2R)-4-(1,3-dimethylpiperidin-4-yl)butan-2-yl group at the 17 position, with double bonds at the 1-10 and 9-19 positions (the 3R,5R,17beta enantiomer).
A pentacyclic sesquarterpene isolated from Bacillus subtilis and formed by cyclisation of (R)-tetraprenyl-beta-curcumene (CHEBI:64801).

A pyochelin that has R-stereochemistry at the thioaminal centre; the diastereoisomer with S-stereochemistry at this centre is pyochelin II. Pseudomonas aeruginosa produces a mixture of pyochelin I (major) and pyochelin II (minor) via condensation of salicylic acid and two molecules of cysteine. The enantiomeric compounds, enant-pyochelin I and II, are produced by Pseudomonas fluorescens.

A pyochelin that has S-stereochemistry at the thioaminal centre; the diastereoisomer with R-stereochemistry at this centre is pyochelin I. Pseudomonas aeruginosa produces a mixture of pyochelin I (major) and pyochelin I (minor) via condensation of salicylic acid and two molecules of cysteine. The enantiomeric compounds, enant-pyochelin I and II, are produced by Pseudomonas fluorescens.
A sphingoid which is the 1-deoxymethylated derivative of 3-dehydrosphinganine.
A bioactive sphingoid which is the 1-deoxymethyl derivative of sphinganine.
A carotenoid having the structure of beta-carotene but with a cis double bond at the 9,10-position.
An EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor which interferes with the action of microbial collagenase (EC 3.4.24.3, also formerly EC 3.4.4.19 and EC 3.4.99.5).

A gamma-lactone that is furan-2(5H)-one which is substituted by a methyl group at position 3 and by a [(1Z,3E)-2-methyl-4-(2,6,6-trimethylcyclohex-1-en-1-yl)buta-1,3-dien-1-yl]oxy group at position 5.
A hydroxyaldehyde in which the hydroxy group is at C-7 of (2E,4E,6E)-4-methylhepta-2,4,6-trienal.
An enal that is the 9-cis-isomer of 10'-apo-beta-carotenal.
A branched C8 alkane, comprising heptane with a methyl group attached at C-4. It has been found in Amaranth seeds.

A diverse group of pharmacologically active secondary metabolite characteristic to Cannabis plant as well as produced naturally in the body by humans and animals. Cannabinoids contain oxygen as a part of the heterocyclic ring or in the form of various functional groups. They are subdivided on the basis of their origin.
An inhibitor that interferes with the process of gap junctional intercellular communication.
A class of cannabinoid which are C21 terpenophenolic compounds isolated primarily from Cannabis sativa.
A class of cannabinoids present in mammalian biological fluids and tissues that activate cannabinoid receptors.
An agonist that selectively binds to and activates a retinoic acid receptor.
An antogonist that interferes with the action of activator protein 1 (AP-1).
A provitamin that can be converted into vitamin A by enzymes from animal tissues.
A class of cannabinoid that consists of synthetic analogs of the naturally occuring cannabinoids.
The hydrochloride salt of N,N'-(p-xylylidene)bis(aminoguanidine) [ratio HCl : N,N'-(p-xylylidene)bis(aminoguanidine) = 2:1].
A guanidine derivative comprised of two carbamimidamido (guanidino) groups, each linked via one of their amino nitrogens to the imino nitrogens of 1,4-phenylenedimethanimine.
The non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is norspermidine (1,5,9-triazanonane) carboxylated with S-configuration at the 2-position.
The dicarboxylic acid that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydrodipicolinic acid hydroxylated at C-4 and with configuration 2S,4S.
A monoterpene ketone in which an (E)-geranyl group is bonded to one of the alpha-methyls of acetone. It is a component of essential oils from various plants including  Nelumbo nucifera.
A terpene ketone derived from ring cleavage of the apo carotenoid beta-ionone.
A ribonucleic acid with two complementary strands, similar to the DNA found in all cells.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcpNAc-1-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol; major species at pH 7.3.

An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of beta-D-Galf-(1->5)-beta-D-Galf-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcpNAc-1-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol; major species at pH 7.3.

An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of beta-D-Galf-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcpNAc-1-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol; major species at pH 7.3.

An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of [beta-D-Galf-(1->5)-beta-D-Galf-(1->6)]14-beta-D-Galf-(1->5)-beta-D-Galf-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcpNAc-1-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the three amino groups of 2'-deamino-2'-hydroxyneamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the two amino groups of 2'-deamino-2'-hydroxy-6'-dehydroparomamine; major species at pH 7.3.
Benzamide substituted on nitrogen by a 2-hydroxyethyl group and at the 4-position by an (N-methylpiperidinio)methyl group.
An organic chloride salt in which the cationic component is 1-{4-[(2-hydroxyethyl)carbamoyl]benzyl}-1-methylpiperidinium.

A tetrol that is cyclohexene in which a hydrogen attached to each of the carbons at positions 3, 4, 5, and 6 is replaced by a hydroxy group. The group consists of six possible diastereoisomers, known as conduritols A to F, some of which can exist as two distinct enantiomers.
A piperidinium ion that is benzamide substituted on nitrogen by a 2-hydroxyethyl group and at the 4-position by a [3-(4-carboxybutanamido)-N-methylpiperidinio]methyl group.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is pregna-4,6-diene-3,20-dione substituted by a methyl group at position 6 and a hydroxy group at position 17.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a tridecasaccharide derivative in which two pentasaccharide branches, each formed from N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannose, are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a trisaccharide chain consisting of mannose and two N-acetylglucosamine residues all linked beta(1->4) with a beta-configuration of the anomeric carbon of the N-acetylglucosamine residue at the reducing end.
A conduritol in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3, and 4 are in a trans,trans,cis- relationship to that at position 1.
A racemate consisting of the two possible cyclohex-5-ene-1,2,3,4-tetrols in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3, and 4 are in a trans,cis,trans- relationship to that at position 1.
An amino cyclitol glycoside that is 2-deoxystreptamine in which the pro-R hydroxy group is substituted by a 6-amino-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl residue.
A conduritol which has 1S,2R,3R,4S configuration.
An amino cyclitol glycoside that is 2-deoxystreptamine in which the pro-R hydroxy group is substituted by a 6-dehydro-alpha-D-glucosyl residue.
A conduritol which has 1R,2S,3S,4R configuration.
An epoxycarotenoid obtained by epoxidation across the 15,15'-double bond of beta-carotene.
